import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Wildlife_Species'])
    chart = sns.countplot(x='Wildlife_Species', data=data, order=data['Wildlife_Species'].value_counts().index)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wildlife species involved in bird strikes?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Aircraft_Make_Model'] = data['Aircraft_Make_Model'].astype('category')
    chart = sns.countplot(x='Aircraft_Make_Model', data=data, order=data['Aircraft_Make_Model'].value_counts().iloc[:10].index)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of aircraft make and models involved in bird strikes?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Effect_Amount_of_damage'])
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Effect_Amount_of_damage', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
